        <section id="ancient-sports">
            <h2>Ancient Sports</h2>
            <p>Sports have been an integral part of human culture for millennia. In ancient times, sports were often associated with religious ceremonies or military training. The ancient Greeks, for example, celebrated athletic competitions such as the Olympic Games, which began in 776 BCE.</p>
            <img src="ancient-olympics.jpg" alt="Ancient Olympic Games">
        </section>

        <section id="modern-sports">
            <h2>Modern Sports</h2>
            <p>With the rise of industrialization in the 19th century, sports evolved into more structured and organized competitions. Modern sports such as football, basketball, and tennis became widespread, and international competitions like the modern Olympic Games were established.</p>
            <img src="modern-sports.jpg" alt="Modern Sports">
        </section>

        <section id="key-events">
            <h2>Key Events in Sports History</h2>
            <p>Throughout the years, there have been defining moments in sports history. From the first manned flight during the early Olympics to record-breaking performances, each of these events has shaped the sports we know today.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="famous-athletes">
            <h2>Famous Athletes</h2>
            <p>Many athletes have become legends in their respective sports. From Muhammad Ali in boxing to Serena Williams in tennis, these athletes have not only achieved greatness in their fields but have also become icons worldwide.</p>
            <img src="famous-athletes.jpg" alt="Famous Athletes">
        </section>
